05/12/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- EU Commissioner for External Relations Chris Patten visits Tirana on Thursday (5 December) for meetings with President Alfred Moisiu, Prime Minister Fatos Nano, Minister of Foreign Affairs Ilir Meta and Minister of State for European Integration Sokol Nako. The focus will be setting an opening date of negotiations for a Stabilisation and Association Agreement and outlining the Commission's intention to conduct a thorough study of Albania's ability to implement the agreement. Patten will also urge leaders to step up the fight against organised crime and corruption. Friday, he heads to Macedonia to discuss implementation of the Ohrid peace accord. (ATA - 04/12/02)
